    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is this 2008 BMW M3 (E92), a purist-spec driver\u2019s car featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8 engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant produces 414 hp with a soaring 8,400 RPM redline, delivered to the rear wheels via a tactile 6-speed manual transmission and a Variable M Differential Lock. The chassis retains its mechanical precision, utilizing a five-link rear suspension and aluminum subframes to minimize unsprung mass. Notably, the rod bearings and throttle actuators\u2014critical maintenance items for this displacement\u2014have been addressed to ensure long-term valvetrain reliability. The Electronic Damping Control (EDC) remains fully functional, offering adjustable compression and rebound cycles for varying road surfaces. While the aesthetic reflects a well-loved enthusiast vehicle with minor stone chips, the drivetrain remains tight with linear power delivery and exceptional throttle response. This is a mechanically sound example of the final naturally aspirated M3, optimized for those who prioritize visceral performance over showroom perfection.",
